The capital asset pricing model (CAPM) is as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{r }_{I}&={\text{R}_{f}} + {{[B}_{I}}{\text{ $\times$ }}{\text{(R}_{m}} - {\text{R}_{f}}{)]}
\end{aligned}$$

Where: 
$$\begin{aligned}
{\text{r}_{I}}& = {\text{Cost of capital for an investment}} \\
{\text{R}_{f}}& = {\text{Risk-free interest rate }} \\
{\text{R}_{m}}& = {\text{Market expected return  }} \\
{\text{B}_{I}} &= {\text{Beta}} 
\end{aligned}$$

We will utilize the reward-to-risk ratio to compute the risk-free rate of the two securities, Pete Corp. and Repete Co. The reward-to-risk ratio occurs until the securities are shown on the same line using the security market line, indicating that they offered the same payoff for taking a risk.

The reward-to-risk ratio is shown as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\dfrac{\text{R }_\text{Pete Corp.}{- }{R}_{f}}{\text{B}_\text{Pete Corp.}}&=\dfrac{\text{R }_\text{Repete Co.}{- }{R}_{f}}{\text{B}_\text{Repete Co.}}
\end{aligned}$$
Where: 
$$\begin{aligned}
{\text{R}_{}}& = {\text{Expected return}} \\
{\text{R}_{f}}& = {\text{Risk-free interest rate }} \\

{\text{B}}&= {\text{Beta}} 
\end{aligned}$$

Now, let us divide both sides by 0.38. This is to cancel out the coefficient of the risk-free rate. This is computed as follows:

$$\begin{aligned}

\dfrac{\text{0.38R}_{f}}{\text{0.38}}&=\dfrac{\text{0.0058  }}{\text{0.38}}\\
&={\textbf{1.53\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The risk-free rate of both assets is 1.53%.**

Then, let us divide both sides by the coefficient of -1.25 to finally determine the market expected return of Pete Corp. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\dfrac{{{- 1.25}} {\text{R}_{m}}}{\text{-1.25}}&=\dfrac{\text{-0.1361}}{\text{-1.25}}\\
{{R}_{m}}&={\textbf{10.89\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The market expected return of Pete Corp. is 10.89%.**

Then, let us divide both sides by the coefficient of -0.87 to finally determine the market expected return of Repete Co. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\dfrac{{{- 0.87}} {\text{R}_{m}}}{\text{-0.87}}&=\dfrac{\text{-0.0947}}{\text{-0.87}}\\
{{R}_{m}}&={\textbf{10.89\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The market expected return of Repete Co. is 10.89%.**
